@startuml notifications-sequence-marketing-preferences
title Marketing preferences (consent capture + gate)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam arrowColor #546E7A

actor Customer
participant "Quote journey\n(frontend)" as UI #ECEFF1
participant "TranzrMoves.Api" as Api #E3F2FD
participant "IMarketingPreferenceService" as Pref #E8F5E9
database "notifications schema" as DB #F3E5F5
queue "RabbitMQ" as RMQ #FFEBEE
participant "SendNotificationHandler" as Handler #E8F5E9

== Quote journey opt-in (explicit) ==
Customer -> UI : Check email / SMS marketing boxes
UI -> Api : PATCH /api/v2/quote/{id}/marketing-preferences\nIf-Match + flags
Api -> Pref : ApplyPreferencesAsync\n(source = QuoteJourney)
Pref -> DB : Upsert CustomerMarketingPreferences\n+ append MarketingConsentEvents

== Preference centre (signed token) ==
Customer -> Api : GET /api/v2/marketing-preferences?token=
Api -> Pref : GetById / ApplyPreferencesAsync\n(source = PreferenceCentre)
Pref -> DB : Update flags + audit event

== Marketing send (future templates — TODO) ==
note over Api, Handler
  True marketing emails use Category = Marketing.
  Templates with preference footer: **TODO** (not quote-reminder).
end note
Api -> RMQ : SendNotification (Marketing)
RMQ -> Handler : Handle(message)
Handler -> Pref : IsChannelEnabledAsync(email, Email)
Pref -> DB : Read CustomerMarketingPreferences
alt EmailMarketingEnabled = false or missing
  Handler -> DB : Record Skipped
else consented
  Handler -> Customer : Send marketing email
end

@enduml
